stories, and to critique himself. Comparison of the novel and its fascinating drafts with the writer's family history reveals increasing preferential treatment of those with greater relatedness to him: kin altruism, i.e., nepotism. This pattern helps explain many of Tolstoy's choices amongst plot variants he considered, as well as some of the curious devices he utilizes to get readers to share his biases, such as coincidences, notions of "fate," and aversion to incest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aNapoleonic Wars.  aRussian literature.  aTolstoy.  aaesthetics.  aancestors.  aautobiographical fiction.  abiopoetics.  acharacter arcs.  aevolutionary psychology.  afamily.  ahistory.  aincest.  akin altruism.  aliterary Darwinism.  anepotism.  aprototypes.  arelationships.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644694091zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644694091423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781644694091.jpg  a978-3-11-068820-7  ASP eBook Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070474-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_